cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for temporal relation extraction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of bootstrapping learning frameworks, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves experimentation with different approaches to improve the performance of the system, which is related to cs.LG (Learning). The use of partially annotated data and the exploration of various usages of it is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
